{"PageNumber":9,"Angle":0,"RotatedAngle":0,"Height":2376,"Width":1836,"OriginHeight":0,"OriginWidth":0,"Elements":[{"Index":0,"Type":"title","Text":"#  Strategy Pattern","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":761,"Y":267},"LeftTop":{"X":761,"Y":219},"RightBottom":{"X":1065,"Y":267},"RightTop":{"X":1065,"Y":219}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":1,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"In Strategy pattern, a class behavior or its algorithm can be changed at run time. This type of design pattern comes under behavior pattern.","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":210,"Y":385},"LeftTop":{"X":210,"Y":302},"RightBottom":{"X":1620,"Y":385},"RightTop":{"X":1620,"Y":302}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":2,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"In Strategy pattern, we create objects which represent various strategies and a context object whose behavior varies as per its strategy object. The strategy object changes the executing algorithm of the context object.","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":210,"Y":559},"LeftTop":{"X":210,"Y":431},"RightBottom":{"X":1620,"Y":559},"RightTop":{"X":1620,"Y":431}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":3,"Type":"title","Text":"##  Components of the Strategy Design Pattern","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":213,"Y":649},"LeftTop":{"X":213,"Y":609},"RightBottom":{"X":884,"Y":649},"RightTop":{"X":884,"Y":609}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":4,"Type":"figure","Text":"","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":542,"Y":1371},"LeftTop":{"X":542,"Y":663},"RightBottom":{"X":1284,"Y":1371},"RightTop":{"X":1284,"Y":663}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":[{"Index":0,"Type":"figure_text","Text":"graph TD     A[Context] --> B[Components]     B --> C[of Strategy Design]     C --> D[Pattern]     D --> E[ConcreteStrategies]","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":542,"Y":1371},"LeftTop":{"X":542,"Y":663},"RightBottom":{"X":1284,"Y":1371},"RightTop":{"X":1284,"Y":663}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":0,"group_type":""}],"ImagePath":"images/024afc5aafcb03147b8fcef95f47f3b4-image.png","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":5,"Type":"title","Text":"###  1. Context","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":213,"Y":1414},"LeftTop":{"X":213,"Y":1383},"RightBottom":{"X":362,"Y":1414},"RightTop":{"X":362,"Y":1383}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":6,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"The Context is a class or object that holds a reference to a strategy object and delegates the task to it.","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":210,"Y":1462},"LeftTop":{"X":210,"Y":1424},"RightBottom":{"X":1545,"Y":1462},"RightTop":{"X":1545,"Y":1424}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":7,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● The Context maintains a reference to a strategy object and calls its methods to perform the task, allowing for interchangeable strategies to be used.","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":267,"Y":1552},"LeftTop":{"X":267,"Y":1469},"RightBottom":{"X":1620,"Y":1552},"RightTop":{"X":1620,"Y":1469}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":8,"Type":"title","Text":"###  2. Strategy Interface","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":213,"Y":1626},"LeftTop":{"X":213,"Y":1588},"RightBottom":{"X":504,"Y":1626},"RightTop":{"X":504,"Y":1588}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":9,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"The Strategy Interface is an interface or abstract class that defines a set of methods that all concrete strategies must implement.","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":210,"Y":1714},"LeftTop":{"X":210,"Y":1628},"RightBottom":{"X":1620,"Y":1714},"RightTop":{"X":1620,"Y":1628}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":10,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● It serves as a contract, ensuring that all strategies adhere to the same set of rules and can be used interchangeably by the Context.","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":267,"Y":1802},"LeftTop":{"X":267,"Y":1716},"RightBottom":{"X":1620,"Y":1802},"RightTop":{"X":1620,"Y":1716}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":11,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● By defining a common interface, the Strategy Interface allows for decoupling between the Context and the concrete strategies, promoting flexibility and modularity in the design.","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":267,"Y":1887},"LeftTop":{"X":267,"Y":1804},"RightBottom":{"X":1620,"Y":1887},"RightTop":{"X":1620,"Y":1804}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":12,"Type":"title","Text":"###  3. Concrete Strategies","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":213,"Y":2148},"LeftTop":{"X":213,"Y":2110},"RightBottom":{"X":522,"Y":2148},"RightTop":{"X":522,"Y":2110}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""}]}